"A good amber IPA which helps transition into the autumn season.  3.7"
"12oz. bottle served in a tulip nonic.  Pours a burnt red hue with a slight haze to the clarity and a loose, quarter inch, light tan head.  Head eventually disperses into a soapy slick.  Diffuse spots and strands of lacing are present during the tasting.   Nose expresses rich malts and intense floral/citrus notes.  Taste is interesting - I almost get a coffee/carmel malt profile integrated with earthy/herbal/citrusy hop notes.  Finishes with an earthy, slightly medicinal bitterness that lingers between quaffs.  Mouthfeel is medium-light with a crisp carbonation and a light acidity.  Overall, there's just a little too much happening here to make it overly drinkable.  It's well-crafted, but not something I need to revisit."
