"Poured from a 12oz bottle (packaged 7/24) into my tulip. Deep reddish hue looked kind of transluscent... little bit of head. Grassy Centennial hops broke through on the nose, a bit of citrus, the ubiquitous SN fresh smell, and a bit of a bitter note. Refreshingly bitter to taste (maybe a bit too bitter), covered up the nice malt character some. Typical light/medium SN body to the IPA style. However crisp, with a nice finish. As much as I like SN, this seemed a typical SN beer. Quite good, but would probably choose something more adventurous next time."
"Pours dark amber/red color with half finger width foamy head.  Head retention and lacing are minimal.  Has an apple, slightly citric aroma, maybe a little bready.  Hop first taste, more grassy than anything else.  Smoother, malty citrus taste follows with a nice bitter aftertaste.  Good beer.  Leaves that nice bitter aftertaste I like with IPAs.  There is a little something off in the transition of malts and hops in this beer."
