"Pours a clear copper color, khaki colored head fades to a thin ring, few splotches of lace. Smell: dried tropical fruit, grapefruit, sharp pine, slightly catty, slightly fruity and brown sugary in the back. Taste: caramel, grapefruit, piney, nectarine towards the finish. Oily, carb pushes to creamy then too far to over carbed, then fades back to oily again. Pretty good, kind of fits an early fall season."
"12oz bottle from a sixer that cost ~$9 so $1.49 per bottle. Dark orange/red color, super huge head which is one thing Sierra Nevada never fails at. The beers always seem to be carbonated just right and have a good mouthfeel. It sort of looks like Celebration. Aroma is hops, pine, honey, pine, tree sap. Flavor is bitter, hoppy, lemons? This is a really subtle but well done beer which is no surprise from Sierra Nevada. Their beers rarely slap you in the face but its hard to say they aren't well-rounded. I went back for another sixer."
