"Lovely copper color, clear body, and two finger thick foamy head made the pour look good in a mug. The aroma was not as hoppy as expected, which did have the benefit of some nutty, caramel malts show through. The taste was also a good deal sweeter than a typical IPA at first, with syrupy first impression. Upon staying longer in the mouth, the beer suddenly seemed to start to get citric, and the finish was quite bitter, with a drawn-out aftertaste. Quite a bit more complex than the first impression, but let down a little by a watery feel."
